                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;As an aside, all-caps variables are &lt;a href=&quot;http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/9699919799/basedefs/V1_chap08.html&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;defined by POSIX&lt;/a&gt; for variable names with meaning to the operating system or shell itself, whereas names with at least one lowercase character are reserved for application use. Thus, consider using lowercase names for your own shell variables to avoid unintended conflicts (keeping in mind that setting a shell variable will overwrite any like-named environment variable).&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/14122/charles-duffy&quot; title=&quot;259,605 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;Charles Duffy&lt;/a&gt;
